name: AbNormal 003 #208
description: Pixel weaving made by glitching out the GL rendering engine in Blender 2.79b, resulting in z-fighting artifacts. The colors come from the normal mat-cap. The interlacing of surfaces is the result of flattening a 3D object into a single plane. Co-planar surfaces become interlaced as rounding errors in the depth buffer create an abstract geometric color field of woven pixels. 3200x2400 png
